{"type":"message","id":"1910285e","parentId":"958e0617","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:04:33.529Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see what's in the backup repo. Let me compare:\n\n**Backup repo content:**\n- `agents`\n- `canvas`\n- `completions`\n- `cron`\n- `delivery-queue`\n- `devices`\n- `flows`\n- `identity`\n- `media`\n- `openclaw-weixin`\n- `openviking`\n- `skills`\n- `tasks`\n- `workspace-main`\n- `workspace-selector` (doesn't exist locally!)\n- `workspace`\n\n**Plus old daily folders:** `2026-04-10/`, `2026-04-12/`\n\n**What exists locally now:**\n- `agents/` вң…\n- `canvas/` - not backed up in current backup.sh\n- `completions/` - not backed up in current backup.sh\n- `credentials/` - not backed up, sensitive\n- `cron/` вң…\n- `delivery-queue/` вң…\n- `devices/` вң…\n- `extensions/` - not backed up (openclaw-lark, openclaw-weixin, openviking, openclawwechat)\n- `feishu/` - not backed up\n- `flows/` вң…\n- `identity/` вң…\n- `memory/` - not backed up (but has `.dreams/`)\n- `openclaw-weixin/` вң…\n- `qqbot/` - not backed up\n- `skills/` - not backed up (main skills)\n- `subagents/` - not backed up\n- `workspace/` вң… (but `memory/.dreams/` inside it?)\n- `workspace-main/` вң…\n- `workspace-skills/` - this is skills inside workspace, which is backed up as part of workspace\n\nWait, `workspace-skills/` is listed in the backup repo but let me check if that dir exists locally.\n\n\nActually I checked earlier - `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` exists and has many skills. But there's also `~/.openclaw/skills/` which is the main skills directory.\n\nSo the actual backup.sh paths from earlier were:\n- `agents/` вң…\n- `workspace/` вң…\n- `workspace-main/` вң…\n- `workspace-selector/` - doesn't exist locally!\n- `workspace/skills/` - wait this is `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` which IS backed up as part of workspace itself\n- `extensions/openviking/` вң… (but extensions/ dir contains more than just openviking)\n\nSo there are TWO separate skills directories: `~/.openclaw/skills/` (the main installed skills) and `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` (workspace-level skills). The backup repo has both `skills/` and `workspace-skills/` as separate top-level directories, but locally they're nested differently - the workspace-skills content is actually inside `workspace/skills/`.\n\nThere's also a `2026-04-10/` and `2026-04-12/` in the backup repo that might be old daily backups. The current backup.sh syncs `openviking/` and `workspace-skills/` separately but seems incomplete.\n\nI need to write a cleaner backup script that handles daily backups with a proper retention policy and gets the directory structure right.\n\nThe key changes: create daily dated folders in the backup repo instead of just syncing to main, clean up what actually needs backing up versus what's redundant, and fix the path mappings between what's local and what's in the repo."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lkw44cix457t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh api repos/59330857/openclaw-backup/contents/2026-04-10 --jq '.[].name' 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776571454946,"responseId":"0633873f714c1a679b81cbcb662e795a"}}
