{"type":"message","id":"f4790b72","parentId":"cc21cfac","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:16:13.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the BACKUP_REPO directory is set to /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone, but the script checks if it has .git and then tries to `cd` into it. But when I `rm -rf` it, the directory doesn't exist, so the `cd` fails. Let me look at the script logic again.\n\n```bash\nif [ -d \"$BACKUP_REPO/.git\" ]; then\n  cd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\n  git checkout \"$GIT_REF\" 2>/dev/null\n  git pull origin \"$GIT_REF\" --quiet\nelse\n  rm -rf \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\n\n\n```\n\nThe else branch has `rm -rf \"$BACKUP_REPO\"` then `git clone`. But if I manually deleted it, the .git directory doesn't exist so it goes to else, which should clone. But the error says \"can't lock config file\" - that's a git error during clone. This might be a network issue or the previous clone was interrupted.\n\nLet me check if the clone actually completed and if there are any lock files left behind. I'll also review the script logic more carefully to see if the set -e is causing the exit on the git error.\n\nThe error about locking the config file suggests either a permissions issue or a corrupted git repo. Let me try cloning fresh to see if that resolves it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_31wq19ph65vu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone 2>/dev/null || echo \"dir does not exist\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776572164925,"responseId":"06338a055d459249089a14f4adebe1fe"}}
