{"type":"message","id":"2bbb4674","parentId":"d2397071","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:17:06.063Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are two issues:\n1. `skills/capability-evolver` and `skills/vibesurf` are themselves git repositories (they have their own `.git` directories), so git is refusing to add them as regular files\n2. `workspace-main/` has a similar issue - it probably contains a `.git` folder (since workspace-main is itself a git repo)\n\nI need to handle these specially. The standard approach is to either:\n1. Use `git add --force` for these directories\n2. Or use `.gitignore` to exclude the `.git` directories within these paths\n3. Or use `rsync` to copy files without the `.git` directories\n\n\n4. Use `rsync` with filters to exclude `.git` subdirectories\n\nThe cleanest approach would be using rsync with `--exclude='.git'` to handle these nested repositories, though I need to verify whether `skills/capability-evolver` and `skills/vibesurf` are truly separate git repos or if they're submodules that need different handling.\n\nActually, the real problem is that `workspace-main` is itself a git repository with its own `.git` folder, so I can't add it as a directory to the backup repo without excluding that `.git` subdirectory. I'll update the rsync command to exclude `.git` directories while preserving the actual git metadata that matters for the backup.\n\nFor `workspace-main` specifically, I need to decide whether to include the workspace content and config files while excluding its internal git history, or treat it differently since it's a distinct repo. Let me focus on the immediate issue: adding the `--exclude='.git'` flag to the rsync commands to prevent git from trying to commit nested repositories as regular files."},{"type":"text","text":"дёӨдёӘеөҢеҘ— git зӣ®еҪ•зҡ„й—®йўҳвҖ”вҖ”capability-evolver е’Ң workspace-main жң¬иә«йғҪжҳҜзӢ¬з«Ӣ git д»“еә“пјҢrsync жҠҠе®ғд»¬зҡ„ `.git` д№ҹеӨҚеҲ¶иҝӣеҺ»дәҶгҖӮдҝ®еӨҚдёҖдёӢпјҡ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v2iqoxqonbit_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rm -rf /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone 2>/dev/null; echo \"cleaned\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776572213095,"responseId":"06338a35c9cc9d1a37672cf9c34f7d20"}}
