{"type":"message","id":"98f971de","parentId":"9766c96a","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:18:24.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! There's actually a `2026-04-19/` directory in the repo already (from the previous partial run that failed at the commit stage). Git status shows it's untracked (`??`). The script says \"No changes\" because `git diff --quiet` only checks tracked files.\n\nSo the 2026-04-19 directory is there but not committed. I need to force-add it. But actually - the `git diff --quiet` check is the issue. If there are untracked files, git diff --quiet returns 0 (no changes to tracked files). So the script skips the commit even though there's an untracked directory.\n \nI see the root cause now: since the 2026-04-19 directory already exists from the previous partial run, the `mkdir -p` command succeeds without creating anything new, so rsync syncs to that existing directory and git status only shows untracked files, which git diff ignores, causing the script to incorrectly skip the commit.\n\nI need to fix the condition to check for untracked files as well, not just modifications to tracked files. Let me verify what's actually in that directory first."},{"type":"text","text":"жңүй—®йўҳвҖ”вҖ”`git diff --quiet` еҸӘжЈҖжҹҘе·Іи·ҹиёӘж–Үд»¶пјҢжјҸжҺүдәҶ untracked зҡ„ `2026-04-19/` зӣ®еҪ•гҖӮйңҖиҰҒдҝ®еӨҚиҝҷдёӘеҲӨж–ӯйҖ»иҫ‘пјҡ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_st5bf6hr132f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-04-19/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776572294500,"responseId":"06338a8679179f53ab7fcbb545f4aaaa"}}
