{"type":"message","id":"a1dfbdb7","parentId":"9fda507d","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:19:16.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, the issue is that the script runs with HOME=/home/halei but in the exec environment HOME might not be set properly, or the rsync_safe function is not finding the source files because of path issues. Let me check...\n\nActually, the issue is simpler - when I ran `bash ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh`, the script uses `$HOME` inside it, and in the exec tool context, `$HOME` might be `/root` instead of `/home/halei`. Let me check."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bpq4ta42rfpr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"HOME=$HOME\" && echo \"е®һйҷ…HOME: $(eval echo ~)\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776572351091,"responseId":"06338abfad7c0b75fba58ff5ac65011d"}}
