`hermes` as the current userвҖ”which apparently isn't finding the command either. The entrypoint runs, fails when trying to exec gosu hermes, then attempts to run hermes directly which also fails with \"command not found\". This suggests either the entrypoint is being overridden by the container's CMD, or gosu isn't available and the exec fallback isn't working as expected. The error persists across all those restart attempts because the same failure is happening each time.\n\nLet me check what the actual CMD is in the container definition and look more carefully at how the entrypoint script handles the privilege dropping - it should be using gosu to switch to the hermes user, but something in that chain isn't working. gosu isn't installed in the image, so the exec command fails and `hermes version` runs as root instead. The error message makes sense now - the entrypoint script tries to use gosu to drop privileges, but since gosu doesn't exist, the fallback to running hermes directly as root also fails. That explains the initial failure before the chown attempt, but then gosu works on subsequent runs and the container appears to start, which is puzzling.\n\nWait, I'm realizing the issue - the image is being built as root but the runtime environment might be different. Let me just check the running container's actual entrypoint and command, then test hermes directly to see what's actually failing."},{"type":"text","text":"ж №жң¬еҺҹеӣ жҳҜ entrypoint йҮҢзҡ„ `gosu` е‘Ҫд»ӨеңЁй•ңеғҸдёӯдёҚеӯҳеңЁпјҢеҜјиҮҙе®№еҷЁеҗҜеҠЁеӨұиҙҘгҖӮзЎ®и®ӨдёҖдёӢпјҡ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xjmustbnloo0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest which gosu 2>&1; echo \"exit:$?\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":177657