{"type":"message","id":"bd833c3f","parentId":"0c6d6f21","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:38:16.925Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The docker-compose.yml doesn't have a `command:` or `entrypoint:` override. So the container should be running the entrypoint.sh. But the actual command being run is `/bin/bash -c 'hermes gateway run'`. This means the entrypoint.sh is being overridden somewhere, or the container was started with a `command:` argument from somewhere else.\n\nWait, but docker-compose.yml by itself doesn't run anything - you need to run `docker-compose up`. Let me check if there's a systemd service or something that runs it.\n\nActually, let me check if there's a startup script or systemd service for hermes-agent."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vxxci8325q4j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user status hermes-agent 2>&1 | head -20; systemctl status hermes 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776573489080,"responseId":"06338f312b389065f31a46ce94356d6c"}}
