{"type":"message","id":"bbd4ab68","parentId":"91617bf5","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:38:32.287Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user ran `docker ps` earlier which showed the container running with `/bin/bash -c 'hermes gateway run'`. But the docker-compose.yml doesn't have a `command:` line, so the command must have been overridden at runtime or there's a different docker-compose/docker run command.\n\nActually, looking again at `docker inspect` output:\n```\n\"Cmd\": [\"-c\", \"hermes gateway run\"]\n\"Entrypoint\": [\"/bin/bash\"]\n```\n\nThis means when the container was started, the entrypoint was overridden to `/bin/bash` and the command was `-c 'hermes gateway run'`. \n\nSo the entrypoint was likely overridden when the container started, not in the compose file since that has neither an entrypoint nor command specified. The command string matches what `docker run` with just a command argument produces, suggesting someone ran `docker run` directly rather than through docker-compose.\n\nThe image itself uses `[/bin/bash]` as entrypoint with `[\"hermes gateway run\"]` as default cmd, but when running interactively with `docker run -it`, the default cmd gets overridden to `/bin/bash -c 'command'`. This likely means the container was started with `docker run -it nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest hermes gateway run` or similar, which sets the entrypoint to `/bin/bash` and passes the command as an argument.\n\nThe error `hermes: command not found` happens because the entrypoint script needs to be `/bin/bash` to source the venv, but the command passed to it references hermes directly without the venv path. When `gosu hermes` runs, it uses a non-interactive shell that doesn't source the venv activation script, so the hermes command isn't found in PATH even though it exists in the venv's bin directory.\n\nThe container keeps restarting with exit code 127 (command not found), which confirms the shell can't locate hermes. I should either remove the custom command to let the entrypoint handle startup properly, or ensure the venv is activated in the shell being executed."},{"type":"text","text":"й—®йўҳзЎ®и®ӨпјҡеҪ“еүҚе®№еҷЁз”Ё `docker run -it ... hermes gateway run` еҗҜеҠЁзҡ„пјҢи·іиҝҮдәҶ entrypoint.shпјҢжүҖд»ҘжІЎжңүжҝҖжҙ» venv и·Ҝеҫ„гҖӮжӯЈзЎ®зҡ„еҗҜеҠЁж–№ејҸжҳҜпјҡ\n\n```\ndocker run -d --name hermes-agent \\\n  -v ~/hermes-data:/opt/data \\\n  -e HERMES_HOME=/opt/data \\\n  -p 18788:18788 \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest\n```\n\nпјҲдёҚдј е‘Ҫд»ӨпјҢи®©е®№еҷЁиө°й»ҳи®Ө entrypoint.shпјҢдјҡиҮӘеҠЁи®ҫзҪ® PATH е№¶иҝҗиЎҢ `hermes gateway run`пјү\n\n**иҰҒжҲ‘зҺ°еңЁйҮҚе»әе№¶йҮҚеҗҜиҝҷдёӘе®№еҷЁеҗ—пјҹ**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776573496983,"responseId":"06338f392eef017e8a2aa972b70827b2"}}
