{"type":"message","id":"b53bcd79","parentId":"80d88800","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:48:12.272Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The container is restarting again. And the logs show it ran `hermes gateway run` but then got \"Goodbye!\" and the container stopped. Let me look at the logs more carefully - the last line says \"Warning: Input is not a terminal (fd=0). Goodbye! вҡ•\" which suggests the process exited.\n\nThe issue might be that `hermes gateway run` requires a TTY or something. Let me look at what the entrypoint runs vs what was being run before.\n\nActually, looking at the logs: it showed the welcome banner, then said \"Goodbye!\" - which means `hermes gateway run` completed/exited. \n\nThe container's now in a restart loop because it keeps exiting instead of staying running. Maybe `hermes gateway run` is the wrong command - perhaps it should just be `hermes gateway` or something else that keeps the process alive.\n\nLooking at the entrypoint.sh, it runs `exec hermes \"$@\"` where \"$@\" would be `gateway run`. Since entrypoint.sh uses `exec`, the hermes process becomes PID 1, so when it exits, the container stops. The real question is why `hermes gateway run` is exiting at all. Let me check if there's a lark/feishu plugin configured for the feishu bot - that might be what's causing it to exit or what's needed to keep it running."},{"type":"text","text":"еҸҲйҮҚеҗҜдәҶвҖ”вҖ”`hermes gateway run` жү§иЎҢе®Ңе°ұйҖҖеҮәдәҶгҖӮжЈҖжҹҘдёҖдёӢйЈһд№ҰжҸ’д»¶й…ҚзҪ®пјҡ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_63swwgx0xeip_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec hermes-agent hermes plugins list 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574080863,"responseId":"063391812443c32be2ffb660952f5dba"}}
