{"type":"message","id":"52a3d39d","parentId":"4d609d75","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:48:40.943Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The container is restarting again. The problem is that the entrypoint starts, runs `hermes gateway run`, it works fine, but then the process exits and the container restarts. This is because `restart: unless-stopped` is set in docker-compose.yml, so when the main process exits, Docker restarts it.\n\nWait - but if it's restarting, that means the `hermes gateway run` command is exiting. The question is why.\n\nActually wait - the logs showed \"Goodbye! вҡ•\" which means the process did exit. But why would `hermes gateway run` exit?\n\nActually, looking at the previous logs again more carefully:\n\n\nThe restart policy keeps kicking in because `hermes gateway run` terminates, which suggests the process itself is crashing or completing. Maybe it's running in the foreground, the terminal detaches, and then it exits? I think the real issue might be that `hermes gateway run` completes successfully and exits, but Docker keeps restarting it because of the `unless-stopped` policy. When I tested it interactively earlier, it worked fine, so there's something about running it in detached mode that causes it to exit. Let me check the logs again to see what the actual error is.\n\nThe \"Restarting (0) 49 seconds ago\" status indicates the container exited with code 0 (success), not a failure, which means `hermes gateway run` likely finished its initialization and terminated. I should try using `hermes gateway start` instead, which is probably the proper daemon command to keep it running in the background."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eprjh3fbi2fh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest hermes gateway --help 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,