{"type":"message","id":"fa6f8c3e","parentId":"03426443","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:49:39.520Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's the actual error! The `hermes gateway run` command is failing because of a feishu (йЈһд№Ұ) import issue:\n\n```\nFile \"/opt/hermes/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/lark_oapi/ws/client.py\", line 17: from lark_oapi.event.dispatcher_handler import EventDispatcherHandler\n...\nKeyboardInterrupt\n```\n\nThe traceback shows `check_tool_availability` is calling `check_feishu` which imports `lark_oapi`, and this fails with some kind of issue.\n\nBut the interesting part is - the log shows \"Dropping root privileges\" TWICE, which means the entrypoint ran twice. \n\nSo the real issue is that `hermes gateway run` is crashing because `lark_oapi` can't be imported - this is a dependency problem in the feishu plugin. I need to check if hermes has a built-in update command to fix this, or if I need to manually reinstall the lark_oapi package in the container."},{"type":"text","text":"жүҫеҲ°дәҶпјҒ`hermes gateway run` еҗҜеҠЁж—¶жҠҘй”ҷпјҡ\n\n```\nFile \"/opt/hermes/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/lark_oapi/ws/client.py\", line 17\n...\nKeyboardInterrupt\n```\n\nйЈһд№ҰжҸ’д»¶зҡ„ `lark_oapi` еә“еҜје…ҘеӨұиҙҘпјҢеҜјиҮҙж•ҙдёӘ gateway ж— жі•еҗҜеҠЁгҖӮйңҖиҰҒеҚҮзә§иҝҷдёӘдҫқиө–пјҡ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p7o99ych5sfy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c 'pip install -q --upgrade lark-oapi 2>&1 | tail -5'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574170316,"responseId":"063391da9ad658fb029f118e7a282717"}}
