{"type":"message","id":"6cc31cd0","parentId":"409180aa","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:49:55.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The venv doesn't have pip either. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe issue is that `lark_oapi` library is failing when importing `lark_oapi.ws.client`. The error is:\n```\nFile \"/opt/hermes/.venv/lib/python3.13/site-packages/lark_oapi/api/translation/__init__.py\", line 1\nfrom . import v1\n```\n\nThis is happening during the `check_tool_availability` phase when the CLI starts. The lark_oapi library has a broken or incompatible version installed in the venv.\n\nOptions:\n1. Mount a updated lark_oapi into the container\n\n\n2. Override the package from the host using volume mounts\n3. Wait for a fix from the Hermes team\n4. Fix the lark_oapi in the container\n\nThe `hermes gateway run` command is what's failing. This command is actually starting a gateway server that processes requests. But it's crashing during startup because when the banner tries to display available toolsets, it checks each toolset's availability, and the Feishu toolset fails when trying to import lark_oapi.\n\nI could try running `hermes gateway` directly without the `run` subcommand to see if that avoids the crash, or I might need to install a newer version of lark_oapi. The cleanest approach would be to upgrade lark_oapi inside the container, but that won't persist across container rebuilds. Alternatively, I could volume mount the updated package or patch it before the gateway starts. Let me check what version of lark_oapi is currently installed first."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bh3zoeuoo0kx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c '/opt/hermes/.venv/bin/python3 -c \"import lark_oapi; print(lark_oapi.__version__)\" 2>&1'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574184898,"responseId":"063391e9a04e31f08de820259d19187d"}}
