{"type":"message","id":"6240eb3e","parentId":"f044c05f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:50:19.052Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `lark_oapi` module exists but is old and has a broken ws component. The issue is that the image has an old version of `lark-oapi` that crashes when trying to import the websocket client. \n\nThis is an image-level issue. We need to either:\n1. Build a custom image with updated lark-oapi\n2. Or fix it by installing the updated version in a way that persists\n\nSince the data is in the volume and we just need to fix the container, one approach is to:\n1. Start the container normally\n2. Run pip install inside the container to upgrade lark-oapi\n3. But the problem is the container keeps restarting\n\n\n4. Wait, maybe the container actually stays running long enough to exec into it if we start it without the restart policy first\n\nLet me try starting it detached without restart, then immediately exec in to upgrade the package."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ihy9ytlqxp2n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run -d --name hermes-agent \\\n  -v /home/halei/hermes-data:/opt/data \\\n  -e HERMES_HOME=/opt/data \\\n  -p 18788:18788 \\\n  --log-opt max-size=10m --log-opt max-file=3 \\\n  nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest \\\n  2>&1; echo \"started\"; sleep 8; docker exec hermes-agent /opt/hermes/.venv/bin/python3 -m pip install --upgrade lark-oapi -q 2>&1 | tail -5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574209344,"responseId":"063392011c54ff11ce5e87649bcc60a2"}}
