{"type":"message","id":"d32c12a2","parentId":"560c66f9","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:52:10.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The default CMD is null (uses ENTRYPOINT). The ENTRYPOINT is `/opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh` which does `exec hermes \"$@\"` and the default \"$@\" seems to be empty or something that causes it to run interactive chat mode instead of `gateway run`.\n\nLet me check what happens when the container runs without any command - it should use the default CMD from the image, but the CMD in the docker-compose file was `\"/bin/bash -c 'hermes gateway run'\"` which overrode the image default.\n\nWait, but the current container was started without any command, just the image name. So it should use the image's default CMD... which is `[\"/bin/bash\", \"-c\", \"hermes gateway run\"]` according to our earlier `docker inspect` of the stopped container.\n \nActually, I need to clarify - when we ran `docker inspect` on the stopped container, we were seeing the configuration that was set at creation time, not the image's original CMD. The image itself has no CMD defined, so the ENTRYPOINT script should be running with whatever default arguments it was designed to use.\n\nLet me trace through what the entrypoint actually does when invoked without arguments - it sources the virtual environment and then executes the hermes command with \"$@\", which would be empty in this case. That would explain why we're seeing the interactive help output instead of the gateway running as a daemon.\n\nBut wait, the \"Warning: Input is not a terminal\" message is the real clue here - that's the gateway starting up in non-interactive mode. The issue is that when it tries to display the welcome banner, it's detecting that there's no actual terminal attached, which triggers that warning and likely causes it to exit or behave differently than expected.\n\nThe container keeps restarting though, which suggests it's not cleanly shutting down - it might be crashing or being killed by Docker's health check mechanism rather than exiting gracefully on its own.\n\nLet me check if there's actually a port 18788 exposed in the image and what process is supposed to be listening there. The gateway command should be starting a server, but if it's not in daemon mode or if the port isn't configured correctly, the container would just exit immediately after the command completes."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j0i7vau1to6k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c 'grep -r \"18788\\|gateway\\|port\" /opt/hermes/*.yaml /opt/hermes/*.json /opt/hermes/docker/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\" | grep -v \".venv\" | head -20'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574313263,"responseId":"06339269b4482af9774bafdbd71bd4ee"}}
