{"type":"message","id":"bb2d1884","parentId":"52b4fe72","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:53:37.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still restarting after ~25 seconds. The container keeps restarting. The problem is that when running in non-interactive mode (no -it), the `hermes gateway run` command exits quickly because stdin is closed. This is the core issue.\n\nLet me look at what `hermes gateway run` actually does and whether there's a way to keep it running in the background without stdin.\n\nActually, let me look at the issue differently. When we ran `docker run -d ... --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c 'sleep 30'`, the container stayed up for 30 seconds. When we ran the actual hermes-agent, it exits in ~25 seconds.\n \nI see the real issue now - the entrypoint script does set up the environment and then executes `hermes \"$@\"`, but since we're not providing any command and the default is likely `gateway run`, it starts the gateway service and then exits because there's no stdin to keep it alive. This is a known problem with services that expect interactive input.\n\nThe docker-compose configuration should use `hermes gateway run` directly as the command rather than wrapping it in `bash -c`, which is causing the stdin issue. Let me check what `gateway run` actually does - it should start the gateway service, but it seems to exit immediately when not connected to a terminal. I should look for flags like `--daemon` or `--background` that might keep it running in the background.\n\nActually, the real issue might be different - looking at the logs more carefully, the gateway starts successfully and displays the banner, then exits with \"Goodbye! вҡ•\", which suggests it's receiving a signal rather than failing on its own. Let me trace what happens between the banner appearing and the shutdown message to understand what's triggering the exit."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zxe9z4hd5x7f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker logs hermes-agent 2>&1 | grep -E \"gateway|Gateway|port|listening|started|running|error|Error\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574404584,"responseId":"063392c5ff7468d2f91ebdaf456b22fd"}}
{"type":"message","id":"72772f0a","parentId":"bb2d1884","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:53:37.293Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zxe9z4hd5x7f_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"в”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":40,"aggregated":"в”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                   mcp: mcporter, native-mcp                  в”Ӯ","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776574417278}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d427943","parentId":"72772f0a","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:53:45.823Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The container keeps restarting and not staying up. The issue is that `hermes gateway run` doesn't run as a long-lived daemon - it runs briefly and then exits (with \"Goodbye! вҡ•\").\n\nLet me think about this differently. The original startup command was `hermes gateway run` and the container was configured with `stdin_open: true` and `tty: true`. This suggests it was meant to run interactively. But now it's exiting immediately.\n\nActually, looking at the original docker-compose.yml more carefully, it had `stdin_open: true` and `tty: true`. This is typically used for interactive containers. But with `hermes gateway run`, which seems to be a daemon mode... hmm.\n \nI think the real problem is that when the entrypoint runs `exec hermes gateway run`, it expects a TTY to be allocated, and without one it exits immediately. The original setup must have been using a different command or startup mechanism to keep it running.\n\nLet me check what the default CMD is in the Dockerfile and whether the recent image update changed something fundamental about how `gateway run` behaves."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h4qsw1hs2lt7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest hermes gateway --help 2>&1 | grep -A3 \"run\\|daemon\\|start\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574417297,"responseId":"063392d1276850dbeb561522b409a5eb"}}
