{"type":"message","id":"8c7db7d3","parentId":"da48dc16","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:54:09.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`hermes gateway run` is the foreground mode. The entrypoint.sh calls `exec hermes \"$@\"` which passes `gateway run` to the hermes command. But it seems like when running in the container, it just prints the banner and exits immediately.\n\nWait - let me re-read the entrypoint.sh. It has `set -e` at the top. If any command fails, the script exits. The gosu command at the end is `exec gosu hermes \"$0\" \"$@\"` where $0 is the script path and $@ is the arguments.\n\nActually, when using `exec gosu hermes \"$0\" \"$@\"`, the $0 and $@ are the arguments to the entrypoint script, not the hermes command. The entrypoint script's arguments would be `gateway run`. So it becomes `exec gosu hermes /opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh gateway run`. That doesn't seem right.\n \nI think I see the issue now. When Docker runs an entrypoint script, `$0` stays as the script path and `$@` contains the CMD arguments. So if the entrypoint is `/opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh` and CMD is `hermes gateway run`, then `$0` becomes `hermes` and `$@` becomes `gateway run`, which gets passed to `exec gosu hermes hermes gateway run` - that's the problem right there.\n\nBut I'm also realizing the `hermes gateway run` command might just be printing the banner and exiting cleanly rather than actually staying running. Let me check if the container is actually crashing or if it's exiting on its own."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_puzm9j23l8hb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run -d --name hermes-test4 \\\n  -v /home/halei/hermes-data:/opt/data \\\n  -e HERMES_HOME=/opt/data \\\n  --log-opt max-size=10m --log-opt max-file=3 \\\n  nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest \\\n  2>&1; echo \"container_id:$?\"; sleep 30; docker ps -a --filter \"name=hermes-test4\" --format \"{{.Status}}\" 2>&1; docker logs hermes-test4 2>&1 | tail -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574437523,"responseId":"063392e68d5dbc76da6d75df49fb8d02"}}
