{"type":"message","id":"3b77f00b","parentId":"7059f644","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:54:57.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The entrypoint is `/opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh` and the default command is null. So the container should be running `hermes gateway run` (since the entrypoint ends with `exec hermes \"$@\"` and no CMD is set, meaning \"$@\" is empty, which means no command passed to `hermes`).\n\nBut the log shows `hermes gateway run` failing with `KeyboardInterrupt` from the feishu tool import error. That was the issue we thought we fixed by the lark_oapi import test passing...\n\nWait, actually in the latest test (hermes-test4), the container exited normally (code 0). The logs show the banner + Goodbye! which means `hermes gateway run` ran and then exited cleanly.\n \nI need to check what happens when `hermes gateway run` gets executed without any arguments. The real issue might be that the default command isn't actually `gateway run` вҖ” if it's running something else or nothing at all, that could explain the clean exit instead of the feishu import error we'd expect."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gthsg5k04lei_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c 'cat /proc/1/cmdline | tr \"\\0\" \" \" ; echo' 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574486621,"responseId":"06339316e9f52a41dfd70e80a3dda80e"}}
