{"type":"message","id":"be2d8f69","parentId":"30329de5","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:55:11.752Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the entrypoint.sh does `exec gosu hermes \"$@\"` but gosu replaces the process, and since no arguments are passed (CMD is null), the gosu process runs `hermes` with no args. Without a TTY and stdin, hermes shows the banner and exits. This is by design when there's no attached session.The container itself is working correctly. The question is about the Feishu integration. The Feishu plugin requires `lark_oapi` which works, but the gateway needs to be running. Let me check if the Feishu platform is actually configured in the hermes data directory.Let me look at the hermes data directory's config to see what messaging platforms are configured."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lupsoz9wgyxk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run -d --name hermes-agent \\\n  -v /home/halei/hermes-data:/opt/data \\\n  -e HERMES_HOME=/opt/data \\\n  -p 18788:18788 \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  --log-opt max-size=10m --log-opt max-file=3 \\\n  nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest \\\n  2>&1 && echo \"started\" && sleep 10 && docker exec hermes-agent hermes gateway status 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574503902,"responseId":"06339328c8b28cf216d249f55feb0514"}}
