{"type":"message","id":"1dfe7dbf","parentId":"9989134e","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:56:09.406Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the container keeps restarting every few seconds. It's running the entrypoint correctly (Dropping root privileges, skill sync), but then `exec hermes \"$@\"` runs with no args (or default args), which runs the CLI interactively and then exits immediately.\n\nThe image must have a default CMD that was set in the Dockerfile before the entrypoint was updated. When the entrypoint is `/bin/bash /opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh` and there's a CMD in the Dockerfile, the CMD overrides the entrypoint's `$@`.\n\nWait, actually the Docker `ENTRYPOINT` + `CMD` combination works like this:\n- `ENTRYPOINT [\"/opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh\"]`\n\n\n- `CMD [\"hermes\", \"gateway\", \"run\"]` вҶҗ this should be passed to the entrypoint as `$@`\n\nBut it's not working. Let me trace through what's actually happening in the running container right now."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rjeqoj0yvisj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c 'cat /Dockerfile 2>/dev/null || echo \"no dockerfile\"; ls /opt/hermes/docker/ 2>/dev/null' 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574560172,"responseId":"06339360f2bf89d56f33f436b02e5c02"}}
