{"type":"message","id":"f50e951a","parentId":"5eff33e5","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:56:34.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the entrypoint script should run with PID 1, and then exec `hermes \"$@\"` as PID 1. But in the container, we see /bin/sh, not hermes. This means either:\n1. The entrypoint script is not running as PID 1 (something else is)2. The entrypoint script is failing before the exec\n\nActually, wait - when running with `--rm`, docker removes the container after the main process exits. The container has PID 1 as the entrypoint. If PID 1 is /bin/sh, it means the entrypoint.sh is NOT running as PID 1.\n\nBut the Entrypoint in the image is `/opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh`. So PID 1 should be that script. Unless... there's some docker runtime thing where if you pass a command override, it wraps it differently.\n \nI should check what the default CMD is in the image without overriding it - that might explain why PID 1 is showing as /bin/sh instead of the entrypoint script."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2910pjypoh14_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run --rm --entrypoint /bin/sh nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest -c 'cat /proc/1/cmdline | xargs -0 echo; cat /proc/1/comm' 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574586005,"responseId":"0633937a22f7b26e675cec95ca11211c"}}
