{"type":"message","id":"2655be15","parentId":"a270dee5","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:57:35.124Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so when I use `--entrypoint /bin/sh`, the actual PID 1 is `/bin/sh -c cat /proc/1/cmdline ...`. This is expected when I override the entrypoint.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The container runs with PID 1 being the entrypoint script. But when I override entrypoint with `/bin/sh`, PID 1 becomes `/bin/sh`.\n\nThe actual issue: why does the container start OK (exit 0) but then immediately exit? The entrypoint runs successfully (we see the \"Done\" message), but then `hermes` exits.\n\nWait, maybe `hermes gateway run` actually starts OK and is listening, but then something kills it. Let me try a different approach - use `hermes gateway run` as the explicit command but keep it attached to see what happens.\n \nLet me try running it in the foreground with stderr captured to see if there's an error being thrown. Or better yet, I'll just invoke `hermes gateway run` directly as the command instead of relying on the entrypoint script."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kni8olsopcl2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run -d --name hermes-agent \\\n  -v /home/halei/hermes-data:/opt/data \\\n  -e HERMES_HOME=/opt/data \\\n  -p 18788:18788 \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  --log-opt max-size=10m --log-opt max-file=3 \\\n  nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest \\\n  hermes gateway run \\\n  2>&1; echo \"===started===\"; sleep 5 && docker logs hermes-agent --tail 10 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574646508,"responseId":"063393b62d3dfe75a04e7522196dc30a"}}
