{"type":"message","id":"95dbdb02","parentId":"d3223886","timestamp":"2026-04-19T04:59:01.862Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me try using --entrypoint to directly run hermes, or use a wrapper script. Since entrypoint.sh ends with `exec hermes \"$@\"`, passing `hermes gateway run` as CMD would make entrypoint run `hermes hermes gateway run`. \n\nThe solution is to use `--entrypoint` to replace the entrypoint entirely, or use `docker exec` in a background loop.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach: use `--entrypoint /opt/hermes/docker/entrypoint.sh` and pass `hermes gateway run` as arguments... but wait, that was already the issue.\n\nActually, the real solution is much simpler: since `hermes` binary is in the venv at `/opt/hermes/.venv/bin/hermes`, we can:\n\n\n1. Use `--entrypoint /opt/hermes/.venv/bin/hermes` and pass `gateway run` as CMD\n2. Or create a wrapper script that sources the venv and runs hermes gateway run\n\nLet me try option 1."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l1ucfrbc7pkf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker run -d --name hermes-agent \\\n  -v /home/halei/hermes-data:/opt/data \\\n  -e HERMES_HOME=/opt/data \\\n  -p 18788:18788 \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  --log-opt max-size=10m --log-opt max-file=3 \\\n  --entrypoint /opt/hermes/.venv/bin/hermes \\\n  nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest \\\n  gateway run \\\n  2>&1; echo \"===started===\"; sleep 10 && docker ps --filter \"name=hermes-agent\" --format \"{{.Status}}\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776574732351,"responseId":"0633940cd196bae229aa6349c20824d7"}}
