{"type":"message","id":"d54ad526","parentId":"258a2b55","timestamp":"2026-04-19T05:13:48.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that Hermes 0.8's Feishu permission confirmations look better than the ones in OpenClaw. He's asking what determines this UI/card style in Feishu messages.\n\nThis is about the Feishu card/message formatting. In Feishu, interactive elements like buttons, confirmation dialogs, etc. can be rendered as \"еҚЎзүҮж¶ҲжҒҜ\" (card messages). The design/appearance of these cards depends on:\n\n1. The card template/schema used by the sending application\n2. The Feishu app's card message configuration\n3. Whether they use the standard Feishu card format or a custom one\n\nFor OpenClaw's Feishu integration, the card rendering depends on how the openclaw-lark plugin constructs the card messages. \n\nFor Hermes, it would depend on its own lark integration. The difference in visual appeal likely comes down to whether they're using Feishu's interactive card format with properly configured action nodes and styling, or just sending basic text messages with external links. Hermes probably invested more effort into crafting a polished card schema with better visual hierarchy and formatting."},{"type":"text","text":"йЈһд№ҰеҚЎзүҮзҡ„йўңеҖјдё»иҰҒеҸ–еҶідәҺ**еҚЎзүҮжЁЎжқҝ/schema зҡ„и®ҫи®Ў**вҖ”вҖ”жҢүй’®еёғеұҖгҖҒйўңиүІжҗӯй…ҚгҖҒдҝЎжҒҜеұӮж¬ЎиҝҷдәӣгҖӮ\n\n Hermes еә”иҜҘеңЁеҸ‘йҖҒжқғйҷҗзЎ®и®Өж—¶з”Ёзҡ„жҳҜ**Feishu дәӨдә’еҚЎзүҮ**пјҲ`card` ж¶ҲжҒҜзұ»еһӢпјүпјҢиҖҢдё”и®Өзңҹи®ҫи®ЎиҝҮжЁЎжқҝгҖӮOpenClaw иҝҷиҫ№зҡ„йЈһд№ҰжҸ’д»¶еҸҜиғҪеҸ‘зҡ„жҳҜз®ҖеҢ–зүҲжҲ–иҖ…ж–Үеӯ—жҢүй’®пјҢи§Ҷи§үдёҠе°ұејұдёҖдәӣгҖӮ\n\nиҝҷжҳҜеҸҜд»ҘдјҳеҢ–зҡ„вҖ”вҖ”ж”№дёҖдёӢйЈһд№ҰжҸ’д»¶йҮҢеҸ‘еҚЎзүҮж—¶з”Ёзҡ„ JSON жЁЎжқҝе°ұиЎҢгҖӮиҰҒжҲ‘еҺ»зңӢдёҖзңј OpenClaw йЈһд№ҰжҸ’д»¶зҺ°еңЁз”Ёзҡ„еҚЎзүҮж јејҸй•ҝд»Җд№Ҳж ·еҗ—пјҹ"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"