{"type":"message","id":"62768a9d","parentId":"78160376","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:38:50.414Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the screenshot, we can see:- **Web URL:** `http://localhost:9119` - This is the web interface port\n- **API URL:** `http://localhost:8642` - This is the API port\n- **Startup Mode:** Manual StartThe container ports are:\n- `18788` mapped to `18788/tcp`But from the earlier logs, we saw:```ERROR gateway.platforms.api_server: [Api_Server] Refusing to start: binding to 0.0.0.0 requires API_SERVER_KEY. Set API_SERVER_KEY or use the default 127.0.0.1.\n```\n\nSo the API server is on port 8642 inside the container. And the web URL 9119 is the Hermes Dashboard.\n\n\nNow I'm realizing the distinction between the gateway and the API server - the gateway is running on 18788, but the API server that powers this web UI is what requires the API_SERVER_KEY to start, and it's configured to bind to 127.0.0.1:8642 inside the container.\n\nFrom the .env file I saw earlier, API_SERVER_ENABLED is true and API_SERVER_PORT is 8642, with API_SERVER_HOST set to 0.0.0.0. The web dashboard likely runs on a separate internal port, so I need to figure out what port that actually uses and whether there's a port mapping for it.\n\nSince the container only exposes 18788, the web dashboard probably isn't accessible from the host unless there's an internal port I'm missing. The most likely scenario is that the API server (8642) and web dashboard are either running inside the container network or using ports that weren't explicitly mapped when the container started. to 8642 on the host, though that would require the container to have been started with that port mapping.\n\nActually, looking at the .env file:\n- API_SERVER_PORT=8642\n- API_SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0\n\nThe API server would be on port 8642 inside the container. But the container only has 18788 mapped. So API server might not be accessible from host.\n\nFor the Web URL (9119), this might be a separate dashboard service that also runs internally.\n\nLet me just give the user the information:\n- The gateway is on port 18788\n- The API server is on port 8642 (but requires API_SERVER_KEY)\n- The Web URL 9119 might not be accessible\n\nThe real issue is that the API server errored out because API_SERVER_KEY isn't set in the .env, so the web dashboard probably can't connect to it. The gateway running on 18788 is separate from the web UI system. I need to find where the web dashboard actually runs and whether the API_SERVER_KEY needs to be configured for the system settings to work properly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3k9zl9xoksak_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec hermes-agent /opt/hermes/.venv/bin/hermes --help 2>&1 | grep -i \"dashboard\\|web\\|gui\\|port\\|9119\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587911558,"responseId":"0633c7877006aeea7629118b21a14045"}}
