{"type":"message","id":"88534e19","parentId":"4d4bdc2a","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:38:59.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I know the answer. The Hermes container exposes port 18788, but the management system screenshot shows Web URL port 9119 and API URL port 8642. \n\nLooking at the `.env` file we saw earlier:\n```\nAPI_SERVER_ENABLED=true\nAPI_SERVER_PORT=8642\nAPI_SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0\n```\n\nSo the API URL would be `http://YOUR_HOST_IP:8642` (where YOUR_HOST_IP is the host machine's IP, not localhost since it's in a container).\n\nFor the Web URL (dashboard), it uses port 9119. Let me check if the dashboard port is exposed.\n\n\nThe container only maps 18788 to the host, but the dashboard runs on 9119 inside the container and the API server on 8642вҖ”neither of these ports are exposed externally. I could either add port mappings when creating the container or use `docker exec` to access them directly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6ti9wal4i3h3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec hermes-agent cat /opt/data/.env 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"API_SERVER|PORT|HOST\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776587930762,"responseId":"0633c79b7c7ee739d668cae2f0944bad"}}
