{"type":"message","id":"7d999c30","parentId":"a82ffddb","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:41:08.059Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pngkxnwzbdq7_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the image provided, here is a breakdown of what the screen displays and the specific error message shown.\n\n### **The Error Message**\nAt the bottom of the screen, in a dark red notification box, a JSON-formatted error message is displayed:\n\n> `{ \"ok\": false, \"error\": \"connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:9119\" }`\n\n**What it means:** The error `ECONNREFUSED` indicates that the software tried to connect to a service running on the local machine (`127.0.0.1`) at port `9119`, but the connection was rejected. This usually happens because the service is not currently running or is not listening on that specific port.\n\n***\n\n### **What the Screen Displays**\nThe image shows a configuration interface for a gateway or dashboard named **\"Hermes.\"** The UI is in dark mode with a mix of Chinese and English text.\n\nThe screen is divided into several sections:\n\n1.  **Hermes Gateway Configuration (Top Section):**\n    *   **Web URL:** An input field set to `http://localhost:18788`.\n    *   **API URL:** An input field set to `http://localhost:8642`.\n    *   **Startup Mode (еҗҜеҠЁж–№ејҸ):** Radio buttons showing \"Manual Start\" (**жүӢеҠЁеҗҜеҠЁ**) is selected. A note below explains that the user needs to manually run the `hermes` command in a terminal to start the dashboard.\n\n2.  **Authentication Configuration (и®ӨиҜҒй…ҚзҪ®):**\n    *   An instruction states that an API Key can be set for identity verification, or left blank to disable authentication.\n    *   **API Key:** An input field currently containing placeholder text.\n\n3.  **Action Buttons:**\n    *   A green **\"Save\" (дҝқеӯҳ)** button.\n    *   A gray **\"Test Connection\" (жөӢиҜ•иҝһжҺҘ)** button.\n\n**Context of the Error:** It appears the user clicked the \"Test Connection\" button, which triggered the connection attempt that resulted in the `ECONNREFUSED` error shown at the bottom. Interestingly, the error references port **9119**, which is different from the Web and API ports configured in the fields above."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/421918a6-bfea-4bb1-9f53-f6c0cd251446.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776588068050}}
{"type":"message","id":"9d7cd478","parentId":"7d999c30","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:41:13.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is `connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:9119`. The system is trying to connect to port 9119, which is different from both the Web URL (18788) and API URL (8642) that were configured. Port 9119 is likely the dashboard/gui service port.\n\nThis means the dashboard isn't running in the container. Let me check - the `hermes dashboard` command is separate from `hermes gateway run`. The dashboard is a web UI for system management.\n\nLet me check if there's a dashboard process running and what port it uses."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3sexax7xvc7v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec hermes-agent /opt/hermes/.venv/bin/hermes dashboard --help 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776588068064,"responseId":"0633c824363fa1a316cea8adf747ad21"}}
{"type":"message","id":"83ab519f","parentId":"9d7cd478","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:41:13.708Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3sexax7xvc7v_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"usage: hermes dashboard [-h] [--port PORT] [--host HOST] [--no-open]\n                        [--insecure]\n\nLaunch the Hermes Agent web dashboard for managing config, API keys, and\nsessions\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help   show this help message and exit\n  --port PORT  Port (default 9119)\n  --host HOST  Host (default 127.0.0.1)\n  --no-open    Don't open browser automatically\n  --insecure   Allow binding to non-localhost (DANGEROUS: exposes API keys on\n               the network)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":308,"aggregated":"usage: hermes dashboard [-h] [--port PORT] [--host HOST] [--no-open]\n                        [--insecure]\n\nLaunch the Hermes Agent web dashboard for managing config, API keys, and\nsessions\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help   show this help message and exit\n  --port PORT  Port (default 9119)\n  --host HOST  Host (default 127.0.0.1)\n  --no-open    Don't open browser automatically\n  --insecure   Allow binding to non-localhost (DANGEROUS: exposes API keys on\n               the network)","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776588073696}}
{"type":"message","id":"697c8818","parentId":"83ab519f","timestamp":"2026-04-19T08:41:24.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The dashboard runs on port 9119 by default, and it's a separate process from the gateway. The user is trying to connect to it but it's not running. We need to start the dashboard separately.\n\nThe dashboard would need to be running for the management UI to connect. Let me start it in the container.\n\nBut wait - the dashboard runs on 127.0.0.1 by default (localhost), and it's running inside the container. To access it from outside the container, we'd need to:\n1. Run with `--host 0.0.0.0 --insecure` \n2. Map port 9119 to the host\n\nHowever, this is a separate binary. We need to run `hermes dashboard` in addition to `hermes gateway run`. \n\nThe current container is only running `hermes gateway run`. I could either start the dashboard as a background process within the same container, or set up a new container specifically for the dashboard with the appropriate port mapping.\n\nActually, the simplest solution is to just restart the container with both the gateway and dashboard processes running together."},{"type":"text","text":"й—®йўҳжҳҜ **DashboardпјҲз®ЎзҗҶз•ҢйқўпјүжІЎиҝҗиЎҢ**гҖӮе®ғйңҖиҰҒеҚ•зӢ¬еҗҜеҠЁпјҢй»ҳи®Өз«ҜеҸЈ `9119`гҖӮ\n\nеҪ“еүҚе®№еҷЁеҸӘи·‘дәҶ `hermes gateway run`пјҢжІЎжңүи·‘ DashboardгҖӮйңҖиҰҒдёҖиө·еҗҜеҠЁпјҡ\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gcgy5isfj6k2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker stop hermes-agent 2>&1; docker rm hermes-agent 2>&1; echo \"cleaned\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776588073715,"responseId":"0633c82a14114f462d29861c0ff7d51d"}}
